<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="450" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1786: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-06T18:00:00-05:00">October 6, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>338. Your 781, October 2, 11 a.m.,<note n="45" xml:id="d450fn45">Not
                                printed.</note> last paragraph. Your suggestion that the Consuls
                            General at Mukden and Harbin be authorized where necessary and
                            appropriate to address the local authorities in regard to claims of
                            American citizens arising in Manchuria, omitting names of such
                            authorities and any Manchukuo designation in the nature of titles and
                            refraining as heretofore from addressing officials of the Manchukuo
                            central régime, has the Department’s approval.</p>
                        <p>Inform Mukden and Harbin.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>